DENGUE -ECUADOR
===============
Date: Sun, 16 Mar 1997 07:49:25 -0500 (EST)
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>
According to the March 15 internet edition of El Comercio [newspaper] in
Quito, Ecuador, during this rainy season there have been 288 cases of dengue
diagnosed in the country. 179 of them in the province of Manabi, 77 in Los
Rios, 26 in El Oro and 6 in Guayas. It is also reported that since 1988
there have been two million cases of clasical dengue diagnosed. The
information was obtained from the System for the Eradication of Malaria and
other Vectors. (Note: 2 million cases over 10 years in a country of ca. 12
million inhabitants? Hard to believe).
---
